01:08:02.279 --> 01:08:05.690
all about sleep. But, the part of it about
sleep, you know...

01:08:05.690 --> 01:08:09.619
[Rhonda]: Really, you know, one of my major
interest is aging, increasing health span,

01:08:09.619 --> 01:08:15.289
as well as performance, without the trade
off, and every time I always come back to

01:08:15.289 --> 01:08:19.850
sleep. The studies, I mean, it just constantly
coming back in my face how important sleep

01:08:19.850 --> 01:08:21.680
is for all those things.

01:08:21.680 --> 01:08:27.859
[Matt]: It's the superordinate lever that
transacts all health benefits, you know. It's

01:08:27.859 --> 01:08:32.570
the tide that rises all of the health boats.
And I think it's wonderful that folks, you

01:08:32.570 --> 01:08:38.330
know, here in Silicon Valley are going after,
you know, individual pathways of disease,

01:08:38.330 --> 01:08:42.770
trying to manipulate, you know, immune pathways
or trying to manipulate mTOR for sort of,

01:08:42.770 --> 01:08:44.990
you know, longevity.

01:08:44.990 --> 01:08:50.160
But I think what's been missing in this equation
is that there is, you know, an Archimedes

01:08:50.160 --> 01:08:55.190
lever here. There is one superordinate node,
that if you pull that lever, all of the other

01:08:55.190 --> 01:09:00.840
pathways are instigated, activated. And that
superordinate node or lever is this thing

01:09:00.840 --> 01:09:06.210
called sleep. You know, there is no physiological
system that we've been able to measure that

01:09:06.210 --> 01:09:10.090
isn't wonderfully enhanced by sleep when you
get it, or demonstrably impaired when you

01:09:10.090 --> 01:09:11.090
don't get enough.

01:09:11.090 --> 01:09:14.180
[Rhonda]: Right. I kind of wanted to go back,
